  "body": "### Description\r\nAs a validator, I want helper functions for deposits processed during the per-block processing logic, so that the client is compliant with the spec and deposits are kept up to date. \r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\nPer-block:\r\n  - Verify that `length` of `block.body.deposits` is <= `MAX_DEPOSITS`\r\n  - For each `deposit` in `block.body.deposits`:\r\n    - Verify that the serialized version of `deposit.deposit_data` matches the `deposit_data` in the Eth 1.0 Deposit Contract spec.\r\n    - Verify that verify_merkle_branch of the (serialized `deposit_data` hash, deposit branch, `DEPOSIT_CONTRACT_TREE_DEPTH`, deposit index, state.latest_eth1_data deposit root) is `TRUE`.\r\n  - Run the `process_deposit` function.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/v0.1/specs/core/0_beacon-chain.md#deposits-1",
